18:34.666 --> 18:38.300 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
And that really affects every
state budget in the country.

18:38.300 --> 18:43.300 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
Every governor receives from the
federal government the largest
amount of federal funds through

18:44.033 --> 18:46.566 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
the Medicaid program.

18:46.566 --> 18:49.666 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
It takes care of disabled
children and adults,
takes care of a lot of
poor seniors in nursing

18:52.400 --> 18:54.466 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
homes.

18:54.466 --> 18:58.033 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
It pays for half of the births
in the country and about 40
percent of children's health

18:58.033 --> 18:59.033 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
insurance.

18:59.033 --> 19:01.133 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
That's the underlying program.

19:01.133 --> 19:05.033 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
You can't cut that program
without really harming services
to the most vulnerable Americans

19:06.500 --> 19:08.933 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
and really blowing up state
budgets across the country.

19:08.933 --> 19:11.033 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
It takes longer, but
it still happens.

19:11.033 --> 19:15.233 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
JUDY WOODRUFF: But I think what
Republicans are arguing is that
Medicaid, as it's presently

19:15.233 --> 19:18.933 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
structured, is unsustainable,
it costs too much for the
federal government, costs too

19:18.933 --> 19:23.233 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
much for the states, and they
say they're taking steps to
make sure that it's there

19:23.233 --> 19:25.233 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
