in nursing homes, for poor
pregnant women and children, for

19:53.333 --> 19:55.433 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
disabled children and adults.

19:55.433 --> 19:58.800 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
They are capping the amount
of federal money that goes.

19:58.800 --> 20:01.133 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
That doesn't change
the population.

20:01.133 --> 20:06.133 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
So all it does is shift costs
to state budgets - - and a lot
of states do not have the extra

20:08.033 --> 20:11.800 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
money -- to local budgets,
or to make sure that
people don't have services.

20:13.800 --> 20:17.633 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
Every pot of money that is
talked about to cover the gap
in services is well under what

20:20.900 --> 20:22.900 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
is being paid for right now.

20:22.900 --> 20:27.433 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
So we're here talking about
opioid treatment and the crisis
that we have across America.

20:29.366 --> 20:32.833 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
There is about $5.5 billion
this year being spent on mental
health services and opioids.

20:35.400 --> 20:40.400 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
Nowhere near that amount
is being proposed as even
a multi-year funding plan.

20:42.866 --> 20:46.000 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
If they take away Planned
Parenthood coverage
from pregnant women
and children, they then

20:46.000 --> 20:48.000 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
have a huge gap in services.

20:48.000 --> 20:52.900 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
So, I don't think they're being
very honest about who gets
affected and what happens to

20:54.600 --> 20:57.133 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
those folks if the money is
cut at the federal level.

20:57.133 --> 21:00.100 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
JUDY WOODRUFF: Let's go
back to the basic complaint
the Republicans have had.

21:00.100 --> 21:02.633 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
KATHLEEN SEBELIUS: Sure.

21:02.633 --> 21:04.666 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
JUDY WOODRUFF: And that
this is, their complaint,
and even Democrats
acknowledge problems and

21:04.666 --> 21:09.600 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
