passed through Congress.

23:15.733 --> 23:18.500 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
It's a huge priority
for Republicans.

23:18.500 --> 23:20.500 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
Is this the beginning of
the end for Obamacare?

23:20.500 --> 23:23.000 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
KATHLEEN SEBELIUS:
It's hard to tell.

23:23.000 --> 23:26.833 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
I think we have a
different conversation
now in America, which is
a good thing, that people

23:29.233 --> 23:33.033 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
now say insurance companies
shouldn't ever again be
allowed to discriminate
against individuals

23:34.200 --> 23:36.166 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
with preexisting
health conditions.

23:36.166 --> 23:39.700 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
That conversation wasn't
even had five years ago.

23:39.700 --> 23:44.533 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
There is some recognition
that health care for
all is a positive step
forward and shouldn't

23:44.533 --> 23:48.666 align:left position:12.5%,start line:80% size:87.5%
be just available
depending on where you
work or where you live.

23:48.666 --> 23:50.666 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
That's a good thing.

23:50.666 --> 23:54.833 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
But what we're actually doing
in the future, I think, is
really important, who loses and

23:55.466 --> 23:57.466 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
who gains.

23:57.466 --> 24:01.633 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
And both the House bill and
the Senate bill fall most
heavily on the sickest, oldest,

24:03.633 --> 24:07.333 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
and lowest-income Americans
and shift those dollars not
into the federal treasury, but

24:08.200 --> 24:10.766 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
to tax breaks for the richest.

24:10.766 --> 24:13.500 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
JUDY WOODRUFF: Kathleen
Sebelius, former secretary
of health and human
services, thank you very

24:13.500 --> 24:14.733 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
much.

24:14.733 --> 24:16.366 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
KATHLEEN SEBELIUS:
Good to be with you.

24:16.366 --> 24:20.466 align:left position:12.5%,start line:80% size:87.5%
JUDY WOODRUFF: And tune
in tomorrow, when I
