HARI SREENIVASAN: And now back
to Judy in Colorado at the
Spotlight Health Conference.

53:19.300 --> 53:23.000 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
JUDY WOODRUFF: Here at
the Aspen conference,
there's conversation
about ways to improve

53:23.000 --> 53:28.000 align:left position:12.5%,start line:80% size:87.5%
health beyond hospitals,
doctors' offices,
and health clubs.

53:30.466 --> 53:33.066 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Some of you may recognize
Joy Crump from her time
as a contestant on the
TV show "Top Chef."

53:35.100 --> 53:40.000 align:left position:12.5%,start line:80% size:87.5%
Joy Crump now runs
three farm-to-table
restaurants in Virginia.

53:40.000 --> 53:43.433 align:left position:12.5%,start line:80% size:87.5%
And she spoke to us
about how the food we
eat affects our health.

53:43.433 --> 53:45.633 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
JOY CRUMP, Restaurant
Owner: My name is Joy Crump.

53:45.633 --> 53:50.300 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
I have three restaurants
in Virginia, and I was on
season 12 of "Top Chef."

53:50.300 --> 53:55.300 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
I'm here at Spotlight
Health to shine a light
on the connectivity
between food and community

53:57.566 --> 53:59.600 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
and your personal health.

53:59.600 --> 54:03.966 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
In the past decade or so,
maybe a little bit beyond that
decade, we really began to drill

54:05.966 --> 54:09.700 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
down into the connection
between locality, where our
food comes from, and health.

54:11.966 --> 54:14.033 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
It's something that
we grew up with.

54:14.033 --> 54:18.100 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
We always grew up going towards
what was closest to us, what
was most readily available, what

54:18.100 --> 54:20.100 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
was in season, and
what was cheapest.

54:20.100 --> 54:22.100 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
It was what tasted best.

54:22.100 --> 54:24.166 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
Those things mattered to us.

54:24.166 --> 54:28.133 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
And now I think, as a
nation, we're insisting
that we understand
where things come from,

54:30.600 --> 54:34.166 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
that we have a correlation
between our food and
our communities in which
our food is produced.

54:36.166 --> 54:38.133 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
The idea that that has to be
expensive or that that is of
a quality level that everyone

54:38.133 --> 54:41.000 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
shouldn't have access
to is sort of ludicrous.

54:41.000 --> 54:43.066 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
It's actually the opposite.

54:43.066 --> 54:47.333 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
You have to get used to eating
the things that don't pass
the test of getting into like

54:47.333 --> 54:52.333 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
a Whole Foods market, but
are still ecologically
sound, locally produced,
organically farmed,

54:55.000 --> 54:58.033 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
picked by hand, traveled a
short distance to get you.

54:58.033 --> 55:00.100 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
They may just have
brown spots on them.

55:00.100 --> 55:03.133 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
You may just be subject to
something that's not so pretty.

55:03.133 --> 55:08.133 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
I can buy a beautiful bushel
of peaches in the middle of the
summer for $40 for a bushel.

55:10.033 --> 55:14.266 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
What I hope to share with young
people that I work with in
the restaurants and even the

55:16.233 --> 55:18.500 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
younger kids that I work with
is a respect for the journey
that food travels in order

55:18.500 --> 55:21.233 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
to get from where it
comes from to our forks.

55:21.233 --> 55:25.733 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
We have to recognize that
farmers bent down and picked
things out of ground in order to

55:25.733 --> 55:27.733 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
get those vegetables
on our plate.

55:27.733 --> 55:32.700 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
Once we do that, I think we
will become less cavalier about
how much we waste, and more

55:34.900 --> 55:38.733 align:left position:12.5%,start line:80% size:87.5%
intent on sharing
and celebrating the
food that we have.

55:38.733 --> 55:42.066 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
JUDY WOODRUFF: Sounds
like good advice to me.

